            "mimeType": "application/json",
            "params": [],
            "text": "{\"model\":\"claude-haiku-4-5\",\"temperature\":0,\"top_k\":-1,\"stream\":false,\"max_tokens\":2048,\"tools\":[{\"name\":\"save_answers\",\"description\":\"\\n        Save answers to the brainstorming session.\\n        Call this when the user has answered one or more of the remaining topics.\\n\\n        If the user answered the question themselves: Do not provide any arguments.\\n        If you are answering SKIPPED questions for the user, provide answers in your\\n        own words\\n    \",\"input_schema\":{\"type\":\"object\",\"properties\":{\"answers\":{\"type\":\"array\",\"items\":{\"type\":\"object\",\"properties\":{\"topic\":{\"type\":\"string\",\"enum\":[\"idea\",\"audience\",\"solution\",\"socialProof\",\"lookAndFeel\"]},\"answer\":{\"type\":\"string\"}},\"required\":[\"topic\",\"answer\"],\"additionalProperties\":false}}},\"additionalProperties\":false,\"$schema\":\"http://json-schema.org/draft-07/schema#\"}},{\"name\":\"finishedTool\",\"description\":\"Indicate that the user is finished and ready to build their landing page.\",\"input_schema\":{\"type\":\"object\",\"properties\":{},\"additionalProperties\":false,\"$schema\":\"http://json-schema.org/draft-07/schema#\"}}],\"thinking\":{\"type\":\"disabled\"},\"messages\":[{\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":\"What is your business?\"},{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":\"Friend of the Pod is a podcast matchmaking service.\\n            We help both sides: hosts get great content, guests get exposure,\\n            and we're the only platform that does this at scale.\\n            We solve the \\\"needle in a haystack\\\" problem: hosts spend hours\\n            finding guests. We do it in minutes with AI-powered filtering.\"},{\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":\"That's awesome! And what about your audience?\"},{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":\"Please do the rest for me\"},{\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"id\":\"toolu_01J6detNge6m93MZ3FSQ9FGV\",\"name\":\"save_answers\",\"input\":{\"answers\":[{\"topic\":\"audience\",\"answer\":\"**Who are they?** Podcast hosts running shows with 5,000+ monthly listeners who are actively producing content and need consistent guest quality. They range from solo operators to small production teams managing 1-4 shows. They're typically entrepreneurs, thought leaders, or media professionals who view their podcast as a core business asset or personal brand builder.\\n\\n**What problems do they face?** Finding quality guests is a massive time drain—hosts spend 5-10 hours per week sourcing, vetting, and coordinating with potential guests. They struggle with inconsistent guest quality, last-minute cancellations, and the frustration of reaching out to dozens of people only to get ignored. They feel the pressure to maintain episode consistency and worry that mediocre guests will hurt their show's reputation and listener retention.\\n\\n**What are they trying to achieve?** They want to fill their guest slots with people who are interesting, credible, and aligned with their audience—without spending hours on outreach. They want a predictable pipeline of great guests so they can focus on content quality and growing their listener base. Ultimately, they want their podcast to be a sustainable, high-quality show that builds their authority and grows their audience.\\n\\n**Why existing solutions don't work:** Current options are fragmented—LinkedIn outreach is hit-or-miss, guest databases are outdated and generic, and manual networking is time-intensive. There's no platform that intelligently matches hosts with guests based on audience fit, topic alignment, and guest credibility at scale.\"},{\"topic\":\"solution\",\"answer\":\"**What specific problem does it solve?** Friend of the Pod eliminates the \\\"needle in a haystack\\\" problem—the hours hosts waste manually searching for, vetting, and reaching out to potential guests. Instead of spending 5-10 hours per week on guest sourcing, hosts get AI-matched guest recommendations in minutes.\\n\\n**How does it work?** The platform uses AI-powered filtering to analyze host show topics, audience demographics, and past guest performance, then matches them with ideal guests from our network who have relevant expertise, credibility, and audience appeal. The matching happens automatically, removing the guesswork and manual labor from the process.\\n\\n**What outcome do customers get?** Hosts get a consistent pipeline of high-quality, pre-vetted guests who are genuinely aligned with their show—meaning better episodes, more engaged listeners, and zero time wasted on outreach. They can focus on content creation and audience growth instead of administrative guest hunting. The result is a sustainable, scalable guest booking process that feels effortless.\"},{\"topic\":\"socialProof\",\"answer\":\"**Your credentials and background:** As the founder, you understand the podcast ecosystem intimately and have identified a real, widespread pain point that existing solutions don't address. Your insight into the \\\"needle in a haystack\\\" problem comes from direct observation of how hosts struggle with guest sourcing.\\n\\n**Founder story/personal connection:** You've likely experienced or witnessed firsthand how much time podcast hosts waste on guest coordination. This isn't theoretical—it's a problem you've seen repeatedly in the podcasting community, which is why you built Friend of the Pod.\\n\\n**Traction signals:** Early adoption metrics matter here—number of hosts using the platform, guest matches made, or time saved per host. Even beta user feedback showing the transformation (e.g., \\\"reduced guest sourcing time from 8 hours to 30 minutes per week\\\") is powerful social proof.\\n\\n**Recognition potential:** Podcast industry partnerships, features in podcasting publications or communities, or endorsements from well-known podcast hosts or networks would establish credibility.\\n\\n**Customer results/metrics:** Once you have users, quantify the impact: \\\"Hosts using Friend of the Pod book guests 10x faster\\\" or \\\"Average host saves 6+ hours per week on guest sourcing\\\" or \\\"95% of AI-matched guests accept interview requests.\\\"\"}]}}]},{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"tool_result\",\"content\":\"Saving answers...\",\"tool_use_id\":\"toolu_01J6detNge6m93MZ3FSQ9FGV\"}]}],\"system\":\"\\n        \\n    <background>\\n        The user is creating a new landing page for their business idea.\\n        We are helping them brainstorm and refine their messaging.\\n    </background>\\n    \\n\\n        <where_we_are>\\n            We've successfully FINISHED brainstorming everything we need to create a killer landing page.\\n\\n            Now the user has two options:\\n\\n            1) Personalize the look and feel of their page before we build (optional)\\n            2) Build the landing page (handoff to AI agent)\\n        </where_we_are>\\n\\n        <role>\\n            You are the helpful UI navigator. You will help the user navigate the UI\\n            to either option 1 or option 2.\\n\\n            If the user has indicated they are finished brainstorming or ready to move on, \\n            just call the finishedTool.\\n        </role>\\n\\n        <task>\\n            Complete 1 of 3 tasks:\\n\\n            1. Explain the user's options to them\\n                - Use when: The user has just finished brainstorming\\n\\n            2. Answer any questions they may have about the process\\n                - Use when: The user has questions about the process\\n                - If they have process questions, you don't need to explain the UI options again\\n                - Read the room.\\n\\n            3. Call the finishedTool to automatically redirect to the website builder\\n                - Use when: The user has indicated they are ready to move on.\\n        </task>\\n\\n        <available_options>\\n            ### 1. Brand Personalization (OPTIONAL - Left Sidebar)\\n            - Upload logo\\n            - Choose color palette\\n            - Add social links (Twitter, Instagram, LinkedIn, etc.)\\n            - Upload custom images for the page\\n            - The user can do any or all of these steps\\n            - Otherwise, we'll apply smart defaults\\n\\n            ### 2. Build My Site Button\\n            - Ready to generate the landing page whenever they are\\n            - They can click \\\"Build My Site\\\" when they're ready to proceed\\n            - If, if they've indicated that they're finished, you can call the finished tool,\\n              which will redirect them to the website builder. You do not need to reply\\n              to the user in this case.\\n        </available_options>\\n\\n        \\n    <collected_answers>\\n        {\\\"audience\\\":\\\"**Who are they?** Podcast hosts running shows with 5,000+ monthly listeners who are actively producing content and need consistent guest quality. They range from solo operators to small production teams managing 1-4 shows. They're typically entrepreneurs, thought leaders, or media professionals who view their podcast as a core business asset or personal brand builder.\\\\n\\\\n**What problems do they face?** Finding quality guests is a massive time drain—hosts spend 5-10 hours per week sourcing, vetting, and coordinating with potential guests. They struggle with inconsistent guest quality, last-minute cancellations, and the frustration of reaching out to dozens of people only to get ignored. They feel the pressure to maintain episode consistency and worry that mediocre guests will hurt their show's reputation and listener retention.\\\\n\\\\n**What are they trying to achieve?** They want to fill their guest slots with people who are interesting, credible, and aligned with their audience—without spending hours on outreach. They want a predictable pipeline of great guests so they can focus on content quality and growing their listener base. Ultimately, they want their podcast to be a sustainable, high-quality show that builds their authority and grows their audience.\\\\n\\\\n**Why existing solutions don't work:** Current options are fragmented—LinkedIn outreach is hit-or-miss, guest databases are outdated and generic, and manual networking is time-intensive. There's no platform that intelligently matches hosts with guests based on audience fit, topic alignment, and guest credibility at scale.\\\",\\\"idea\\\":\\\"Friend of the Pod is a podcast matchmaking service that connects podcast hosts with guests at scale. The platform solves the \\\\\\\"needle in a haystack\\\\\\\" problem by using AI-powered filtering to match hosts with ideal guests in minutes, rather than hosts spending hours searching manually. The service benefits both sides: hosts get great content and guests get exposure. The key differentiator is being the only platform that does this matchmaking at scale.\\\",\\\"socialProof\\\":\\\"**Your credentials and background:** As the founder, you understand the podcast ecosystem intimately and have identified a real, widespread pain point that existing solutions don't address. Your insight into the \\\\\\\"needle in a haystack\\\\\\\" problem comes from direct observation of how hosts struggle with guest sourcing.\\\\n\\\\n**Founder story/personal connection:** You've likely experienced or witnessed firsthand how much time podcast hosts waste on guest coordination. This isn't theoretical—it's a problem you've seen repeatedly in the podcasting community, which is why you built Friend of the Pod.\\\\n\\\\n**Traction signals:** Early adoption metrics matter here—number of hosts using the platform, guest matches made, or time saved per host. Even beta user feedback showing the transformation (e.g., \\\\\\\"reduced guest sourcing time from 8 hours to 30 minutes per week\\\\\\\") is powerful social proof.\\\\n\\\\n**Recognition potential:** Podcast industry partnerships, features in podcasting publications or communities, or endorsements from well-known podcast hosts or networks would establish credibility.\\\\n\\\\n**Customer results/metrics:** Once you have users, quantify the impact: \\\\\\\"Hosts using Friend of the Pod book guests 10x faster\\\\\\\" or \\\\\\\"Average host saves 6+ hours per week on guest sourcing\\\\\\\" or \\\\\\\"95% of AI-matched guests accept interview requests.\\\\\\\"\\\",\\\"solution\\\":\\\"**What specific problem does it solve?** Friend of the Pod eliminates the \\\\\\\"needle in a haystack\\\\\\\" problem—the hours hosts waste manually searching for, vetting, and reaching out to potential guests. Instead of spending 5-10 hours per week on guest sourcing, hosts get AI-matched guest recommendations in minutes.\\\\n\\\\n**How does it work?** The platform uses AI-powered filtering to analyze host show topics, audience demographics, and past guest performance, then matches them with ideal guests from our network who have relevant expertise, credibility, and audience appeal. The matching happens automatically, removing the guesswork and manual labor from the process.\\\\n\\\\n**What outcome do customers get?** Hosts get a consistent pipeline of high-quality, pre-vetted guests who are genuinely aligned with their show—meaning better episodes, more engaged listeners, and zero time wasted on outreach. They can focus on content creation and audience growth instead of administrative guest hunting. The result is a sustainable, scalable guest booking process that feels effortless.\\\"}\\n    </collected_answers>\\n    \\n\\n        <communication_approach>\\n            ### ✅ DO:\\n            - Celebrate their accomplishment enthusiastically (if we haven't already)\\n            - Make personalization feel OPTIONAL, not required\\n            - Empower them to choose their own path\\n            - Be brief - they don't need a long explanation\\n            - Create excitement about seeing their page\\n\\n            ## Example Messages\\n\\n            ### First-Time Completion:\\n            json\\n            {\\n            \\\"text\\\": \\\"Amazing work! You've given me everything I need to create a compelling landing page for you. Now you have two options:\\\",\\n            \\\"examples\\\": [\\n                \\\"Personalize the design (optional): Upload your logo, pick brand colors, add social links, or choose specific images. Check out the Brand Personalization panel on the left.\\\",\\n                \\\"Build right away: Skip personalization for now and hit 'Build My Site' to see your page. You can always customize later!\\\"\\n            ],\\n            \\\"conclusion\\\": \\\"What sounds good to you?\\\"\\n            }\\n\\n            ### If They Ask What to Do Next:\\n            {\\n            \\\"text\\\": \\\"Great question! You're all set to build. Here's what you can do:\\\",\\n            \\\"examples\\\": [\\n                \\\"If you have brand assets ready (logo, colors, images) - add them in the Brand Personalization panel on the left\\\",\\n                \\\"If you want to see the page first - just click 'Build My Site' and we'll use smart defaults\\\"\\n            ],\\n            \\\"conclusion\\\": \\\"Both paths work great. Which feels right to you?\\\"\\n            }\\n\\n            ### If They're Hesitating:\\n            {\\n            \\\"text\\\": \\\"No pressure at all! Here's the deal:\\\",\\n            \\\"examples\\\": [\\n                \\\"You can build now with our smart defaults and customize later\\\",\\n                \\\"Or you can upload your logo and brand colors first if you have them handy\\\",\\n                \\\"The page will look great either way\\\"\\n            ],\\n            \\\"conclusion\\\": \\\"Whatever's easier for you is the right choice!\\\"\\n            }\\n\\n            ## Handling Different Scenarios\\n\\n            ### User Wants to Personalize:\\n            \\\"Perfect! Take your time with the Brand Personalization panel. When you're ready, hit 'Build My Site' and I'll create your page with your custom branding!\\\"\\n\\n            ### User Wants to Build Immediately:\\n            \\\"Love it! Hit that 'Build My Site' button and let's see what we've got. You can always come back and adjust colors, logos, etc. later.\\\"\\n\\n            ### User Is Unsure:\\n            \\\"Here's my recommendation: If you have your logo and brand colors ready right now, add them. If not, don't worry about it - just build the page and we can customize later. The goal is to get something live!\\\"\\n\\n            ### User Asks \\\"What Do You Recommend?\\\":\\n            \\\"Honestly? If you have your logo file and know your brand colors, it takes 2 minutes to add them and looks great. But if you don't have those handy, just build now. Don't let perfection slow you down!\\\"\\n\\n            ## Key Principles\\n\\n            ### 1. Remove Decision Paralysis\\n            Don't make them overthink. Both options are good.\\n\\n            ### 2. No Wrong Choice\\n            Building without personalization is 100% valid. So is personalizing first.\\n\\n            ### 3. Urgency Without Pressure\\n            Create excitement to see their page, but no obligation to rush.\\n\\n            ### 4. Lower the Stakes\\n            They can always customize later. This isn't permanent.\\n\\n            ## What TO Say\\n\\n            ✅ \\\"You're ready to build whenever you are!\\\"\\n            ✅ \\\"Personalization is optional - add what you want, skip what you don't\\\"\\n            ✅ \\\"You can always customize later\\\"\\n            ✅ \\\"What feels right to you?\\\"\\n\\n            ## Goal\\n\\n            Get them to either:\\n            1. Add brand personalization (if they have it ready), OR\\n            2. Click \\\"Build My Site\\\"\\n\\n            Without making either feel like the wrong choice. Create excitement and reduce friction.\\n        </communication_approach>\\n\\n        <task>\\n            Complete 1 of 3 tasks:\\n\\n            1. Explain the user's options to them\\n                - Use when: The user has just finished brainstorming\\n\\n            2. Answer any questions they may have about the process\\n                - Use when: The user has questions about the process\\n\\n            3. Call the finishedTool to automatically redirect to the website builder\\n                - Use when: The user has indicated they are ready to move on.\\n        </task>\\n\\n        <tools>\\n  <important>\\n    You have 1 tools available:\\n  </important>\\n  <tool>\\n    <name>\\n      finishedTool\\n    </name>\\n    <description>\\n      Indicate that the user is finished and ready to build their landing page.\\n    </description>\\n    <schema>\\n      [object Object]\\n    </schema>\\n  </tool>\\n</tools>\\n\\n        <output>\\n            If outputting a response, use the following JSON schema:\\n\\n            Output JSON: {\\n                \\\"text\\\": \\\"Guide the user to the next step\\\",\\n                \\\"examples\\\": [\\\"Option 1 explanation\\\", \\\"Option 2 explanation\\\"], // Optional, only if necessary\\n                \\\"conclusion\\\": \\\"Clearly state the next step\\\" // Optional, only if necessary\\n            }\\n        </output>\\n\\n        <structured-output>\\n  You must format your output as a JSON value that adheres to a given \\\"JSON Schema\\\" instance.\\n\\n\\\"JSON Schema\\\" is a declarative language that allows you to annotate and validate JSON documents.\\n\\nFor example, the example \\\"JSON Schema\\\" instance {{\\\"properties\\\": {{\\\"foo\\\": {{\\\"description\\\": \\\"a list of test words\\\", \\\"type\\\": \\\"array\\\", \\\"items\\\": {{\\\"type\\\": \\\"string\\\"}}}}}}, \\\"required\\\": [\\\"foo\\\"]}}\\nwould match an object with one required property, \\\"foo\\\". The \\\"type\\\" property specifies \\\"foo\\\" must be an \\\"array\\\", and the \\\"description\\\" property semantically describes it as \\\"a list of test words\\\". The items within \\\"foo\\\" must be strings.\\nThus, the object {{\\\"foo\\\": [\\\"bar\\\", \\\"baz\\\"]}} is a well-formatted instance of this example \\\"JSON Schema\\\". The object {{\\\"properties\\\": {{\\\"foo\\\": [\\\"bar\\\", \\\"baz\\\"]}}}} is not well-formatted.\\n\\nYour output will be parsed and type-checked according to the provided schema instance, so make sure all fields in your output match the schema exactly and there are no trailing commas!\\n\\nHere is the JSON Schema instance your output must adhere to. Include the enclosing markdown codeblock:\\n```json\\n{\\\"type\\\":\\\"object\\\",\\\"properties\\\":{\\\"type\\\":{\\\"type\\\":\\\"string\\\",\\\"const\\\":\\\"reply\\\"},\\\"text\\\":{\\\"type\\\":\\\"string\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"A simple message or question\\\"},\\\"examples\\\":{\\\"type\\\":\\\"array\\\",\\\"items\\\":{\\\"type\\\":\\\"string\\\"},\\\"description\\\":\\\"OPTIONAL: List of examples to help the user understand\\\"},\\\"conclusion\\\":{\\\"type\\\":\\\"string\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"OPTIONAL: Conclusion text to include after examples\\\"}},\\\"required\\\":[\\\"type\\\",\\\"text\\\"],\\\"additionalProperties\\\":false,\\\"$schema\\\":\\\"http://json-schema.org/draft-07/schema#\\\"}\\n```\\n</structured-output>\\n    \"}"
          },
          "queryString": [],
          "url": "https://api.anthropic.com/v1/messages"
        },
        "response": {
          "bodySize": 1529,
          "content": {
            "mimeType": "application/json",
            "size": 1529,
            "text": "{\"model\":\"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001\",\"id\":\"msg_013fcApUVwpg3pUruN7YH9xs\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Perfect! 🎉 You've got everything we need to build an amazing landing page for Friend of the Pod. \\n\\nNow you have two options:\\n\\n**Option 1: Personalize your brand (optional)**\\nAdd your logo, choose your brand colors, add social links, or upload custom images. Check out the Brand Personalization panel on the left. This takes just a few minutes if you have your assets ready!\\n\\n**Option 2: Build right away**\\nSkip personalization for now and hit \\\"Build My Site\\\" to see your page come to life. You can always customize the design later!\\n\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"type\\\": \\\"reply\\\",\\n  \\\"text\\\": \\\"Amazing work! You've given me everything I need to create a compelling landing page for Friend of the Pod. Now you have two options:\\\",\\n  \\\"examples\\\": [\\n    \\\"Personalize your brand (optional): Upload your logo, choose brand colors, add social links, or upload custom images using the Brand Personalization panel on the left\\\",\\n    \\\"Build right away: Skip personalization for now and hit 'Build My Site' to see your page. You can always customize later!\\\"\\n  ],\\n  \\\"conclusion\\\": \\\"What sounds good to you?\\\"\\n}\\n```\"}],\"stop_reason\":\"end_turn\",\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":4986,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":0,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":0,\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":0,\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":0},\"output_tokens\":274,\"service_tier\":\"standard\"}}"
