            "mimeType": "application/json",
            "size": 1469,
            "text": "{\"model\":\"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001\",\"id\":\"msg_01WXTWqWwBzDG7QVXMXEyoPw\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"I appreciate the enthusiasm, but let's stay focused! 😊\\n\\nYou've got a solid concept with **Friend of the Pod** as a podcast matchmaking service. Now I need to understand what makes it special.\\n\\nHere's what I'm asking: **Who are you matching with whom, and what's your secret sauce?**\\n\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"type\\\": \\\"reply\\\",\\n  \\\"text\\\": \\\"You mentioned Friend of the Pod is a podcast matchmaking service—that's a great starting point. But I need to understand the core differentiation. Are you matching listeners to podcasts? Hosts to guests? Brands to shows? And what makes your matching process better than what already exists?\\\",\\n  \\\"examples\\\": [\\n    \\\"We match listeners to niche podcasts based on their values and interests (not just algorithm)\\\",\\n    \\\"We match podcast hosts with ideal guest experts using personality compatibility\\\",\\n    \\\"We match advertisers with podcasts where their ideal customers actually listen\\\"\\n  ],\\n  \\\"conclusion\\\": \\\"What's the specific problem you're solving, and who benefits most from your service?\\\"\\n}\\n```\"}],\"stop_reason\":\"end_turn\",\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":2498,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":0,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":0,\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":0,\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":0},\"output_tokens\":242,\"service_tier\":\"standard\"}}"
