          "bodySize": 1373,
          "content": {
            "mimeType": "application/json",
            "size": 1373,
            "text": "{\"model\":\"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001\",\"id\":\"msg_01B9hurCf6F9g1Xas8VWfjYm\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"I hear you—pasta is amazing! But let's channel that passion into **Friend of the Pod**. 😄\\n\\nI need you to focus here: **What is Friend of the Pod actually doing?** You've given me the name and that it's a matchmaking service, but I need the real differentiator.\\n\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"type\\\": \\\"reply\\\",\\n  \\\"text\\\": \\\"Let's get specific about Friend of the Pod. I need to understand: Who are you matching? (listeners to podcasts? hosts to guests? brands to shows?) And what makes your matching process different or better than existing solutions?\\\",\\n  \\\"examples\\\": [\\n    \\\"We use personality assessments to match listeners with podcasts that align with their values\\\",\\n    \\\"We connect podcast hosts with guest experts who have complementary audiences\\\",\\n    \\\"We match sponsors with podcasts based on audience fit, not just download numbers\\\"\\n  ],\\n  \\\"conclusion\\\": \\\"Give me 2-3 sentences on what Friend of the Pod does and why it's different.\\\"\\n}\\n```\"}],\"stop_reason\":\"end_turn\",\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":2763,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":0,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":0,\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":0,\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":0},\"output_tokens\":233,\"service_tier\":\"standard\"}}"
          },
